           SPELL=gnomevfs-mount
         VERSION=0.2.0
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.bz2
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://primates.ximian.com/~sandino/$SPELL/files/$SOURCE
          MD5[0]=66c3899f444a692e882142638de0ca73
       BUILD_API=2
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
        WEB_SITE=http://primates.ximian.com/~sandino/gnomevfs-mount/
         ENTERED=20041113
         UPDATED=20041113
           SHORT=" A program for mounting gnome-vfs-uris (directories inside uris) onto the linux filesystem."
cat << EOF
Just do gnomevfs-mount uri_to_mount mount_directory.
gnomevfs-umount umounts mounted uris.
Optional. When mounting restricted uris, like ssh: or ftp:/, it asks gnome-keyring
for a stored user and pass. Otherwise, just it asks a password in a plain prompt.
File info structures are keeped in a cache, so listing directories is faster than before.
EOF
